       options:

	 -v, --verbose                        verbose output of informations
	 -f, --fatal                          make warnings errors
	 -ns, --noscripting                   do not write index-files
	 -r, --recurse                        recurse extracting

	input-basics:

	 -p, --palette <palette>              quake palette lump
	 -c, --colormap <colormap>            quake colormap lump
	 -pp, --preprocessor "<commandline>"  you can specify a preprocessor like cpp to parse
			 		      QuakeC-files before the compiler. if you want to give
			 		      commandlines to it, it is a must to set quotation-marks
	 				      (eg. "cpp -P" is perfectly valid), afterwards qtools inter-
	 				      prets the commandline for itself
	 -dd, --destdir <destdir>             alternative destination directory including "/" at the end
	 -l, --darkness <darkness>            take this darkness-level
	 -lz, --compress                      compress data with lz77 (only for wads)
	 -mip0, --onlymip0                    store only the first mip instead of all four (only
			 		      for wads)
	 -dt, --dither [<value>]              dither floyd-steinberg with this error
			 		      (a little bit complicate: the standard error diffusion
			 		       with floyd steinberg is to divide by 16 and add con-
			 		       stant parts of the error to neighnour pixels. the value
			 		       is valid from 16 to 256 which means: is the error-ammount
			 		       for a pixel 3 we use 3/16 of the error in default. if the
			 		       amount is 32 we use 3/32, so the error-diffusion is halfed.
			 		       in general we could say, the higher the value, the less
			 		       qtools do error-diffusion (an invinite value means NO
			 		       error-diffusion, in practice the errors maximum is 256).
			 		       default is 16.
	 -sm, --smooth [<value>]              smooth the pictures while converting (valid from 1 to 256)
			 		      meaning, all upto 256th of the 8 neighbour-pixels influences
			 		      the original pixel-color. default is 2.
	 -light, --light		      if bsp calculate light too
	 -pvs, --pvs			      if bsp calculate pvs (vis) too
	 -cs, --complete-search               if searching for anim-frames, continue after FirstNotFound,
					      animations like +0,+7,+O are possible

	output-modifications:

	 -o, --outfile <file>                 specify archive-content or output-name
	 -ppm/-jpg/-png/-iff,
	  --output-ppm/jpeg/png/ilbm	      convert pictures and palettes to ppm/jpg/png
	 -wv, --wide-view                     if view mipmaps display all mip-levels

	input-modifications

         -a, --archive-name <name>            use this name to load the file and input-name as
				              archive-entry that is a bit confusing, see below)
	 -vis, --type-is-vis                  use inputfile(s) as vis-lump fors bsps
	 -lit, --type-is-light                use inputfile(s) as light-lump fors bsps
	 -mip, --type-is-mipmap               use inputfile(s) as raw-mipmap
	 -wal, --type-is-wal                  use inputfile(s) as raw-wal
	 -lmp, --type-is-lump                 use inputfile(s) as raw-lump

